\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 06, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104adp1665702785903.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/adp1665702785903.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/adp1665702785903.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"adp1665702785903\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Open an\n    Editor</h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can open editors of components, IncludeScript and snippets from the Project. You can open editors for global objects from the menu.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"adp1665702785903__p_d3596e1_d3597e1_d3598e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xok1665702686298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xok1665702686298.html\" title=\"Each main development object is opened in its own editor.\">Open a Main Development Object for Editing</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"adp1665702785903__p_d3599e1_d3600e1_d3601e1\">Each main development object is opened in its own editor, which is displayed as a tab of a Uniface IDE window.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"adp1665702785903__p_d3602e1_d3603e1_d3604e1\">The Uniface IDE allows you to have 2 windows open, each of which can contain multiple editors. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cth1665702785978.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cth1665702785978.html\" title=\"The Uniface IDE allows you to have two windows open at the same time. The secondary window cannot contain the output tabs. You can move an editor between windows using the editor tab's context menu.\">Open or Close the Secondary IDE Window</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"adp1665702785903__p_d3605e1_d3606e1_d3607e1\">If you have not created any objects yet, create a project, then create other objects in the project. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bcl1665702619726.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bcl1665702619726.html\" title=\"Projects are used to organize your application's development objects. They are the starting point fort application development, and are used to create new main development objects.\">Create a Project</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"okr1665702619654.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/okr1665702619654.html\" title=\"New development objects may be created using templates and modeled objects. For main development objects, such as components and entities, it is also possible to create new object by duplicating an existing object.\">Create a New Development Object</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525637\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525637\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Open an Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 06, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Open an Editor You can open editors of components, IncludeScript and snippets from the Project. You can open editors for global objects from the menu. For more information, see Open a Main Development Object for Editing . Each main development object is opened in its own editor, which is displayed as a tab of a Uniface IDE window. The Uniface IDE allows you to have 2 windows open, each of which can contain multiple editors. For more information, see Open or Close the Secondary IDE Window . If you have not created any objects yet, create a project, then create other objects in the project. For more information, see Create a Project and Create a New Development Object . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}